This is because _height_ is declared as _[static](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/classvars.html)_, thus cannot be accessed from the _non-static_, _instance_ method.

```java
class Rectangle {
    double width, height;

    Rectangle(double sideLength) {
        width = height = sideLength;
    }

    Rectangle(double width, double height) {
        this.width = width;
        this.height = height;
    }

    public double computeArea() {
        return width * height;
    }

    public double computePerimeter() {
        return 2 * (width + height);
    }

    public double getHeight() {
        return height;
    }

    public double getWidth() {
        return width;
    }
}
```

Alternately, use a _[record](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/language/records.html)_.

```java
record Rectangle(double width, double height) {
    Rectangle(double sideLength) {
        this(sideLength, sideLength);
    }
    
    public double computeArea() {
        return width * height;
    }
    
    public double computePerimeter() {
        return 2 * (width + height);
    }
}
```

